PARLIAMENT - Parliament held a special sitting on Tuesday afternoon where MPs expressed their condolences following the passing of Ahmed Kathrada.The family of the ANC struggle stalwart turned down an offer to attend the ceremony to honour him.They cited short notice and other commitments.The family sent out a statement saying a better way for MPs to pay homage would be to support a vote of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma.Kathrada died in hospital three months ago, following a bout of pneumonia he'd contracted after brain surgery.* Watch the full video report by Leigh-Anne Jansen in the gallery above.The official list of speakers is embedded below: eNCA